for business, is it?

132
00:06:20,447 --> 00:06:21,715
Oh, it's
for charity, sir.

133
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:23,951
People are awfully good
about it, you know.

134
00:06:23,984 --> 00:06:25,152
Oh, I see.

135
00:06:25,185 --> 00:06:27,287
Right, sir, I'll get
you a senior assistant.

136
00:06:27,321 --> 00:06:28,388
Ants, was it?

137
00:06:28,422 --> 00:06:29,756
Yes, please.

138
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,025
Mr. snetterton?

139
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:33,060
I don't want him!

140
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:34,595
Oh, please,
give me a chance.

141
00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:35,629
No!

142
00:06:35,662 --> 00:06:37,231
All right, mr. hartford.

143
00:06:37,264 --> 00:06:39,800
Yes, good morning, sir,
can I help you?

144
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:42,069
Yes, please, I'm interested
in buying an ant.

145
00:06:42,102 --> 00:06:44,905
Ah, yes, and what price were
you thinking of paying, sir?

146
00:06:44,938 --> 00:06:47,407
Oh, well, I hadn't
actually got as far as that.

147
00:06:47,441 --> 00:06:49,610
Well, sir, they start
about half a p

